CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782047474
OL,3,CFrance restricts public drinking and
OL,4,Coutdoor sports as heatwave hits Europe
OL,6,FThe Eiffel Tower and other Paris
OL,7,Fvenues set up misting stations to cool
OL,8,Fcrowds, among a raft of measures
OL,9,Fannounced by national and local
OL,10,Fauthorities to minimise risks.
OL,12,FFrance's annual Music Day on Sunday is
OL,13,Fa particular concern for authorities.
OL,14,FThe nationwide summer solstice
OL,15,Fcelebration involves thousands of
OL,16,Fconcerts in village squares, rave
OL,17,Fvenues and Paris clubs, bringing
OL,18,Fcommunities together and increasingly
OL,19,Fdrawing international visitors.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
