PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1782047474
OL,3,CFrance restricts public drinking and
OL,4,Coutdoor sports as heatwave hits Europe
OL,6,FMore than 200,000 people across Europe
OL,7,Fdied from heat-related causes over the
OL,8,Flast four years, and most of the
OL,9,Ffatalities were preventable, the World
OL,10,FHealth Organisation's Europe office
OL,11,Fsaid this month.
OL,13,FWHO's Europe office called for
OL,14,Fcountries and institutions to
OL,15,Fimplement heat plans, such as opening
OL,16,Fcooling centres, or introducing breaks
OL,17,For flexible shifts that enable workers
OL,18,Fto stay out of the midday sun.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
